 of her personal life, as well as the catalyst for her professional transformation into \\\"The Barefoot Contessa.\\\"\", \"from\": 3305, \"to\": 3439, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The city\", \"from\": 3305, \"to\": 3313}, {\"ngram\": \"a key part\", \"from\": 3317, \"to\": 3327}, {\"ngram\": \"her personal life\", \"from\": 3331, \"to\": 3348}, {\"ngram\": \"the catalyst\", \"from\": 3361, \"to\": 3373}, {\"ngram\": \"her professional transformation\", \"from\": 3378, \"to\": 3409}, {\"ngram\": \"The Barefoot Contessa\", \"from\": 3416, \"to\": 3437}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In speaking on the podcast \\\"Dishing on Julia,\\\" released in conjunction withHBO's Julia Child series, Garten describes the first time she and her husband, economist Jeffrey Garten, visited France.\", \"from\": 3440, \"to\": 3635, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3521, \"end\": 3532, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julia_Child\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Julia Child\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julia_Child\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julia_Child\"}, {\"begin\": 3604, \"end\": 3618, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeffrey_Garten\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jeffrey Garten\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeffrey_Garten\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeffrey_Garten\"}, {\"begin\": 3628, \"end\": 3634, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999996307452, \"rank\": 3.68669034674192e-10, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the podcast\", \"from\": 3455, \"to\": 3466}, {\"ngram\": \"Julia\", \"from\": 3479, \"to\": 3484}, {\"ngram\": \"Garten\", \"from\": 3541, \"to\": 3547}, {\"ngram\": \"the first time\", \"from\": 3558, \"to\": 3572}, {\"ngram\": \"her husband\", \"from\": 3581, \"to\": 3592}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They brought a tent, all kinds of camping gear, a tiny camping stove and $5 a day for food.\", \"from\": 3636, \"to\": 3727, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a tent\", \"from\": 3649, \"to\": 3655}, {\"ngram\": \"all kinds\", \"from\": 3657, \"to\": 3666}, {\"ngram\": \"camping gear\", \"from\": 3670, \"to\": 3682}, {\"ngram\": \"a tiny camping stove\", \"from\": 3684, \"to\": 3704}, {\"ngram\": \"food\", \"from\": 3722, \"to\": 3726}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We could not afford to go to a restaurant,\\\" Garten said with a laugh.\", \"from\": 3728, \"to\": 3798, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a restaurant\", \"from\": 3758, \"to\": 3770}, {\"ngram\": \"Garten\", \"from\": 3773, \"to\": 3779}, {\"ngram\": \"a laugh\", \"from\": 3790, \"to\": 3797}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I had to go to the markets and buy food and cook in the tent, and that's where I learned about French markets.\\\"\", \"from\": 3799, \"to\": 3911, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3895, \"end\": 3901, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9999971643768917, \"rank\": 2.8319115701960727e-06, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the markets\", \"from\": 3815, \"to\": 3826}, {\"ngram\": \"food\", \"from\": 3835, \"to\": 3839}, {\"ngram\": \"the tent\", \"from\": 3852, \"to\": 3860}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There, Garten said, she foundpeachesthat tasted like peach jam, a kaleidoscopic array of cheeses and crispy, handmade French baguettes.\", \"from\": 3913, \"to\": 4048, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4031, \"end\": 4037, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9999971643768917, \"rank\": 2.8319115701960727e-06, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Garten\", \"from\": 3920, \"to\": 3926}, {\"ngram\": \"peach jam\", \"from\": 3966, \"to\": 3975}, {\"ngram\": \"a kaleidoscopic array\", \"from\": 3977, \"to\": 3998}, {\"ngram\": \"cheeses\", \"from\": 4002, \"to\": 4009}, {\"ngram\": \"crispy\", \"from\": 4014, \"to\": 4020}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All in all, a real departure from a trip to an American supermarket.\", \"from\": 4049, \"to\": 4117, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4096, \"end\": 4104, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9985114572462928, \"rank\": 0.0014907606723129174, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"All in all, a real departure\", \"from\": 4049, \"to\": 4077}, {\"ngram\": \"a trip\", \"from\": 4083, \"to\": 4089}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That was an era, in 1971 - it was like Wonder Bread,\\\" Garten said.\", \"from\": 4119, \"to\": 4186, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4159, \"end\": 4171, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wonder_Bread\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Wonder Bread\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wonder_Bread\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wonder_Bread\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an era\", \"from\": 4129, \"to\": 4135}, {\"ngram\": \"Garten\", \"from\": 4174, \"to\": 4180}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"You could not even get a freshly baked loaf of bread.\\\"\", \"from\": 4187, \"to\": 4242, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a freshly baked loaf\", \"from\": 4211, \"to\": 4231}, {\"ngram\": \"bread\", \"from\": 4235, \"to\": 4240}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After spending four months in France, Garten became \\\"enamored\\\" with French food.\", \"from\": 4244, \"to\": 4324, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4274, \"end\": 4280, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999996307452, \"rank\": 3.68669034674192e-10, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 4312, \"end\": 4318, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9999971643768917, \"rank\": 2.8319115701960727e-06, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"four months\", \"from\": 4259, \"to\": 4270}, {\"ngram\": \"Garten\", \"from\": 4282, \"to\": 4288}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Upon the young couple's return to the United States, she bought both volumes of Julia Child's \\\"Mastering the Art of French Cooking.\\\"\", \"from\": 4325, \"to\": 4457, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4363, \"end\": 4376, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999998753992, \"rank\": 1.2450512973192042e-10, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the young couple's return\", \"from\": 4330, \"to\": 4355}, {\"ngram\": \"both volumes\", \"from\": 4389, \"to\": 4401}, {\"ngram\": \"Julia Child\", \"from\": 4405, \"to\": 4416}, {\"ngram\": \"the Art\", \"from\": 4430, \"to\": 4437}, {\"ngram\": \"French Cooking\", \"from\": 4441, \"to\": 4455}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That was really the beginning of my culinary education, my self-education,\\\" Garten said.\", \"from\": 4459, \"to\": 4548, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the beginning\", \"from\": 4476, \"to\": 4489}, {\"ngram\": \"my culinary education\", \"from\": 4493, \"to\": 4514}, {\"ngram\": \"Garten\", \"from\": 4536, \"to\": 4542}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the decades since, Garten has consciously introduced American audiences to the best parts of French cooking, while also dispelling some long-held misconceptions about the cuisine and culture.\", \"from\": 4550, \"to\": 4744, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4606, \"end\": 4614, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9985114572462928, \"rank\": 0.0014907606723129174, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 4646, \"end\": 4660, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_cuisine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French cooking\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_cuisine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_cuisine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the decades\", \"from\": 4553, \"to\": 4564}, {\"ngram\": \"Garten\", \"from\": 4572, \"to\": 4578}, {\"ngram\": \"the best parts\", \"from\": 4628, \"to\": 4642}, {\"ngram\": \"some long-held misconceptions\", \"from\": 4684, \"to\": 4713}, {\"ngram\": \"the cuisine\", \"from\": 4720, \"to\": 4731}, {\"ngram\": \"culture\", \"from\": 4736, \"to\": 4743}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Americans think of French food as fancy food, and it's true that some French food is elaborate and formal,\\\" Garten wrote in her seminal 2004 book, \\\"Barefoot in Paris.\\\"\", \"from\": 4745, \"to\": 4913, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4765, \"end\": 4771, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9999971643768917, \"rank\": 2.8319115701960727e-06, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 4816, \"end\": 4822, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9999971643768917, \"rank\": 2.8319115701960727e-06, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 4906, \"end\": 4911, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.1630020193463806e-21, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Americans\", \"from\": 4746, \"to\": 4755}, {\"ngram\": \"fancy food\", \"from\": 4780, \"to\": 4790}, {\"ngram\": \"Garten\", \"from\": 4854, \"to\": 4860}, {\"ngram\": \"her seminal 2004 book\", \"from\": 4870, \"to\": 4891}, {\"ngram\": \"Barefoot\", \"from\": 4894, \"to\": 4902}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She continued: \\\"But there are so many kinds of French food.What I love is simple, country French that is easy enough to make every day but special enough to serve for a party.\", \"from\": 4915, \"to\": 5090, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4962, \"end\": 4968, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9999971643768917, \"rank\": 2.8319115701960727e-06, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 5005, \"end\": 5011, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9999971643768917, \"rank\": 2.8319115701960727e-06, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"so many kinds\", \"from\": 4945, \"to\": 4958}, {\"ngram\": \"a party\", \"from\": 5082, \"to\": 5089}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So that's what this book is all about.\\\"\", \"from\": 5091, \"to\": 5130, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this book\", \"from\": 5106, \"to\": 5115}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I'd always go to the street markets and I wished I had an oven, so I could just take a chicken home and roast it.\\\"\", \"from\": 5132, \"to\": 5247, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the street markets\", \"from\": 5150, \"to\": 5168}, {\"ngram\": \"a chicken home\", \"from\": 5218, \"to\": 5232}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While many viewers of \\\"Barefoot Contessa,\\\" Garten's beloved television series that ran for 19 years on the Food Network, associate the host with her now-iconic kitchen in the Hamptons, Garten has also maintained an apartment in Paris for nearly 25 years, something that she actually began wishing for the very first time she and Jeffrey toured the city, camping tent in tow.\", \"from\": 5249, \"to\": 5623, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5272, \"end\": 5289, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barefoot_Contessa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Barefoot Contessa\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barefoot_Contessa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barefoot_Contessa\"}, {\"begin\": 5356, \"end\": 5368, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Food_Network\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.38737098727523e-59, \"text\": \"Food Network\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Food_Network\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Food_Network\"}, {\"begin\": 5477, \"end\": 5482, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.1630020193463806e-21, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 5578, \"end\": 5585, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeffrey_Spender\", \"score\": 0.986475240822983, \"rank\": 0.01371018368439991, \"text\": \"Jeffrey\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeffrey_Spender\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeffrey_Spender\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"many viewers\", \"from\": 5255, \"to\": 5267}, {\"ngram\": \"Garten's beloved television series\", \"from\": 5292, \"to\": 5326}, {\"ngram\": \"19 years\", \"from\": 5340, \"to\": 5348}, {\"ngram\": \"the host\", \"from\": 5380, \"to\": 5388}, {\"ngram\": \"her now-iconic kitchen\", \"from\": 5394, \"to\": 5416}, {\"ngram\": \"the Hamptons\", \"from\": 5420, \"to\": 5432}, {\"ngram\": \"Garten\", \"from\": 5434, \"to\": 5440}, {\"ngram\": \"an apartment\", \"from\": 5461, \"to\": 5473}, {\"ngram\": \"nearly 25 years\", \"from\": 5487, \"to\": 5502}, {\"ngram\": \"the very first time\", \"from\": 5550, \"to\": 5569}, {\"ngram\": \"the city\", \"from\": 5593, \"to\": 5601}, {\"ngram\": \"tow\", \"from\": 5619, \"to\": 5622}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"When I used to go there just on vacation for a week, I'd always go to the street markets and I wished I had an oven, so I could just take a chicken home and roast it,\\\" Garten said in a 2012 interview withFodor's.\", \"from\": 5623, \"to\": 5836, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"vacation\", \"from\": 5656, \"to\": 5664}, {\"ngram\": \"a week\", \"from\": 5669, \"to\": 5675}, {\"ngram\": \"the street markets\", \"from\": 5694, \"to\": 5712}, {\"ngram\": \"a chicken home\", \"from\": 5762, \"to\": 5776}, {\"ngram\": \"Garten\", \"from\": 5792, \"to\": 5798}, {\"ngram\": \"a 2012 interview withFodor\", \"from\": 5807, \"to\": 5833}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Garten's apartment is, fittingly, right off of Boulevard Raspail, which hosts the same market the TODAY Show crew visited with Garten.\", \"from\": 5838, \"to\": 5972, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5885, \"end\": 5902, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boulevard_Raspail\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Boulevard Raspail\", \"types\": [\"Q34442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/